                                                                                                               Good Morning
      Hello It's Wednesday , August 5 , 2009                    
	Penguin lecture    The third Penguin Annual Lecture, Justice  and India by Amartya Sen, at Nandan, 6.30pm. Barkha Dutt will be in conversation with the Nobel laureate after the lecture.    
	Theatre    Staging of Rabindranath Tagores Rabibar (Sunday) directed by Sohag Sen at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6.30pm.    
	Workshop    Workshop on handicrafts, conducted in collaboration with the Crafts Council, at Bharatiyam Cultural Multiplex, 11am to 5pm.     
	Art watch    Works by Kalyan Sundar Gupta at Academy of Fine Arts, 3pm to 8pm.    Charcoal works by Ajay De at Gallery Nakshatra, 11.30am to 7.30pm.    Monsoon Mosaic, a selection of works by various artists, at The Art Shoppe gallery, 11am to 7pm.    Works by Sujata Chakraborty at The Promenade Lounge, Taj Bengal, 10am to 11pm.    Rare glimpse of rare art at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm.    Works by Alakananda Mukerji at GC Laha Centenary Fine Arts Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.                                                                                                                                                                   
